						<summary>

						<p>Slab in front of the Kēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Dundubhi, Āshāḍha śu. 5.</hi> On the basis of palaeography, it may be assigned to the 16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record an agreement given by Mummaḍi Nāyuḍu, the <hi rend="italic">kāryakartta</hi> of <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Nandyēla Nāraparāju-Kṛishṇappadēva-mahārāja to the share-holders of the village.</p>						

						</summary>
